A table of the data. There are
three columns: Student, Gender, and SSHA Score. Gender is the
Explanatory variable, and SSHA Score is the Response variable.
Some example data:
    Student 1, Female, 154;
    Student 2, Female, 109;
    Student 3, Male, 108;
    Student 4, Female, 115;
    ... (abbreviated) ...
    Student 40, Male, 140;
